      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This guide will show you how to use Service Bus topics and subscriptions from Ruby applications.",
      "pos": [
        562,
        658
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The scenarios covered include <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>creating topics and subscriptions, creating subscription filters, sending messages<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to a topic, <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>receiving messages from a subscription<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>deleting topics and subscriptions<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        659,
        874
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information on topics and subscriptions, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Next Steps<ept id=\"p1\">](#next-steps)</ept> section.",
      "pos": [
        875,
        967
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What are Service Bus Topics and Subscriptions",
      "pos": [
        972,
        1017
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Service Bus topics and subscriptions support a <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>publish/subscribe\nmessaging communication<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> model.",
      "pos": [
        1019,
        1118
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When using topics and subscriptions,",
      "pos": [
        1119,
        1155
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "components of a distributed application do not communicate directly with",
      "pos": [
        1156,
        1228
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "each other, they instead exchange messages via a topic, which acts as an",
      "pos": [
        1229,
        1301
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "intermediary.",
      "pos": [
        1302,
        1315
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "TopicConcepts",
      "pos": [
        1319,
        1332
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In contrast to Service Bus queues, where each message is processed by a",
      "pos": [
        1410,
        1481
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "single consumer, topics and subscriptions provide a <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>one-to-many<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> form",
      "pos": [
        1482,
        1554
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "of communication, using a publish/subscribe pattern.",
      "pos": [
        1555,
        1607
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is possible to",
      "pos": [
        1608,
        1625
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "register multiple subscriptions to a topic.",
      "pos": [
        1626,
        1669
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When a message is sent to a",
      "pos": [
        1670,
        1697
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "topic, it is then made available to each subscription to handle/process",
      "pos": [
        1698,
        1769
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "independently.",
      "pos": [
        1770,
        1784
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A topic subscription resembles a virtual queue that receives copies of",
      "pos": [
        1786,
        1856
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "the messages that were sent to the topic.",
      "pos": [
        1857,
        1898
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can optionally register",
      "pos": [
        1899,
        1926
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "filter rules for a topic on a per-subscription basis, which allows you",
      "pos": [
        1927,
        1997
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "to filter/restrict which messages to a topic are received by which topic",
      "pos": [
        1998,
        2070
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "subscriptions.",
      "pos": [
        2071,
        2085
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Service Bus topics and subscriptions enable you to scale to process a",
      "pos": [
        2087,
        2156
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "very large number of messages across a very large number of users and",
      "pos": [
        2157,
        2226
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "applications.",
      "pos": [
        2227,
        2240
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Create a Service Namespace",
      "pos": [
        2245,
        2271
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To begin using Service Bus queues in Azure, you must first create a service namespace.",
      "pos": [
        2273,
        2359
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A service namespace provides a scoping container for addressing Service Bus resources within",
      "pos": [
        2360,
